Holland beat Kazakhstan 3-1 in Amsterdam on Friday to pick up their first points in Group A.

Second half goals from Klaas-Jan Huntelaar, Ibrahim Afellay and Robin van Persie sealed victory for Guus Hiddink's side after Rinat Abdulin had given the visitors a shock lead in the 18th minute.

